message.content:
Amanita flavoconia is a type of poisonous mushroom species.
It has a distinct yellow to yellow-orange cap with a smooth texture.
The cap is around 5-15 cm wide and convex or flat in shape.
The stem is also yellow, often with white patches, and has a partially or fully removable ring.
Underneath the cap, it has white free gills that are closely packed together.
It is commonly found growing in wooded areas on the ground, especially under oak trees.
Consuming this mushroom can cause severe poisoning symptoms, including nausea, vomiting, and liver damage.
